'''Tryton''' is a three-tiers high-level general purpose application platform under the license GPL-3 written in Python and using PostgreSQL as database engine.

It is the core base of a complete business solution ([[Wikipedia:Enterprise_resource_planning|ERP]]) providing modularity, scalability and security.

== Installation ==

First step: install PostgreSQL, following [[PostgreSQL|wiki entry]].
{{Emerge|postgresql-server}}

Second step: install layman, following [[Layman|wiki entry]].
{{Emerge|layman}}

Third step: install Tryton layout, following [http://code.google.com/p/tryton/wiki/GentooOverlay tryton instructions].
{{RootCmd|layman -a tryton}}

Fourth step: install Tryton server and clients
{{Emerge|trytond}}
{{Emerge|tryton sao}}

== Server configuration ==

The server options are setup in {{Path|/etc/conf.d/trytond}}
The options are:
* <code>CONFIG</code>: the path to the [http://doc.tryton.org/tip/trytond/doc/topics/configuration.html#topics-configuration tryton configuration] (ex: <code>/etc/trytond/trytond.conf</code>)
* <code>LOGCONF</code>: the path to the [http://doc.tryton.org/tip/trytond/doc/topics/logs.html#logging-configuration logging configuration] (ex: <code>/etc/trytond/log.conf</code>)

{{Note|There is no minimal configuration required but it will use SQLite database.}}

To use the web client, you must add this section to the configuration file:

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/trytond/trytond.conf|lang=ini|1=
[web]
root=/usr/share/sao
}}

Don't forget start the database server.

For PostgreSQL:
{{RootCmd|/etc/init.d/postgresql start}}
For MySQL:
{{RootCmd|/etc/init.d/mysql start}}

Setup the database following: [http://doc.tryton.org/tip/trytond/doc/topics/setup_database.html#how-to-setup-a-database]

You can start the server now:
{{RootCmd|/etc/init.d/trytond start}}
If you want to start the server when de system boot up:
{{RootCmd|rc-update add trytond default}}

== Client configuration ==

You can configure the tryton client just running the application:

{{Cmd|tryton}}

The client ask you about Json-rpc and database connection. Create a new profile with the next data:
<pre>
Server: localhost:8000
Database: database name
Username: admin
</pre>

{{Note|You need to create a new database.}}

== Modules installation ==

Initially, you only have 3 modules: ir, res. To install other modules you can watch the {{Path|app-tryton}} folder: {{Path|/var/lib/layman/tryton/app-tryton}}. You can find the tryton modules. Install what you need:
{{Emerge|app-tryton/account}}
...
After that you need to tell the database that there is new modules installed, for that:

{{RootCmd|/usr/bin/trytond -c <config_file> -d <db_name> -u account}}
or
{{RootCmd|/usr/bin/trytond -c <config_file> -d <db_name> --all}}

